  <h2 id="negotiation">Negotiation Vocabulary</h2>

  <p>Chinese negotiations tend to be longer and more relationship-focused than Western ones. Patience is essential — rushing signals desperation. A common tactic in Chinese business negotiations is to build a strong personal relationship before discussing terms. Do not be surprised if the first meeting — or even the first few meetings — involve little actual negotiation and focus instead on getting to know each other. This process, while time-consuming, lays the groundwork for trust that makes the eventual deal stronger and more durable.</p>

